cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI 

The paper deals with the registration and fusion of lidar and aerial imagery for creating accurate maps for autonomous vehicle navigation. This involves computer vision techniques for processing the imagery, robotics for the lidar data acquisition, and machine learning for the fusion of the data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with robotics and autonomous vehicles, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics). The use of GIS (Geographic Information Systems) is also mentioned, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for the fusion of the data, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the creation of accurate maps for autonomous vehicle navigation, which involves AI techniques, and hence falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
